result.execSummary:
The defendant Brittany K. Ackley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Brittany K. Ackley in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:53 AM. State - resolved - plead g/nc to #2 as alleged, dismiss and read in #1, joint recommendation of a withheld sentence and place on probation for 1 year with conditions of: costs, AODA and follow thru, anger management and/or psychological, no consumption of possession of alcohol and no entry into any bas, taverns or liquor stores, employment/school, 25 hours of community service. Burns and Ackley agree. Court dismisses and reads in count #1. Ackley pleads NC to count #2 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State - follow joint recommendation. Burns - follow joint recommendation, recommends expungement. Ackley withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #2 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 1 year with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, anger management assessment and if treatment is recommended - complete it and follow thru, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, 25 hours of community service within first 4 months, costs - paid thru probation, credit for 1 day only if revoked, eligible for expungement upon successful completion of probation, right to appeal, adjourned.

Defendant Brittany K. Ackley in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:00 PM. State - Burns does not have all discovery as State just realized there is a disc that she did not receive. Court will allow another adjournment, continues bond, set for another FPT.  Final pre-trial scheduled for April 22, 2015 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Brittany K. Ackley in court.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:30 AM. Ackley does not have complaint. Court reads charges and penalties and right to attorney and court appointed attorney. Ackley understands charges and penalties. Recess to talk to SPD. Recalled at 10:16 AM, now appears with Mary Burns. Burns waives further reading, enters NG pleas, set for FPT on 4/15/15 at 1:15 PM. Back on record at 10:18 AM, defendant has hearing difficulties so court repeated everything and defendant heard and understood.
